vars: {
  d2-config: {
    layout-engine: elk
    theme-id: 6
  }
}

title: |'md
## State Machine: SHA256_CTX Lifecycle
`sha256_init` · `sha256_update` · `sha256_finalize` · reuse
'| {
  near: top-center
}

# ── States ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

UNINITIALIZED: {
  shape: rectangle
  style: {
    fill: "#2d1b4e"
    stroke: "#9b72cf"
    stroke-width: 2
    font-color: "#e8d5ff"
    border-radius: 8
  }
  label: |'md
**UNINITIALIZED**
`H[0..7]` = garbage
`buf_len`  = undefined
`total_bits` = undefined
'|
}

INITIALIZED: {
  shape: rectangle
  style: {
    fill: "#1a3a2a"
    stroke: "#4caf7d"
    stroke-width: 3
    font-color: "#c8f0db"
    border-radius: 8
  }
  label: |'md
**INITIALIZED**
`H[0..7]` = SHA256_INITIAL_HASH
`buf_len`  = 0
`total_bits` = 0
*Invariant: no partial block buffered*
'|
}

ACCUMULATING: {
  shape: rectangle
  style: {
    fill: "#1a2a3e"
    stroke: "#4a90d9"
    stroke-width: 3
    font-color: "#c8e0ff"
    border-radius: 8
  }
  label: |'md
**ACCUMULATING**
`H[0..7]` = running hash state
`buf_len`  ∈ [1, 63]
`total_bits` = Σ(len×8) so far
`buf[0..buf_len-1]` = valid bytes
*Invariant: buf never holds full block*
'|
}

BLOCK_BOUNDARY: {
  shape: rectangle
  style: {
    fill: "#3a2a10"
    stroke: "#e6a020"
    stroke-width: 3
    font-color: "#ffe8b0"
    border-radius: 8
  }
  label: |'md
**BLOCK_BOUNDARY**
*(transient — no external visibility)*
`buf_len` reached 64
→ `sha256_compress(H, buf)`
→ `buf_len` reset to 0
*Resolved within single update() call*
'|
}

FINALIZED: {
  shape: rectangle
  style: {
    fill: "#3a1a1a"
    stroke: "#e05050"
    stroke-width: 3
    font-color: "#ffd0d0"
    border-radius: 8
  }
  label: |'md
**FINALIZED**
`digest[0..31]` = valid SHA-256 output
`H[0..7]` = final state (stale)
`buf` = padding + length field (stale)
*ctx is indeterminate — must re-init*
'|
}

ILLEGAL_USE: {
  shape: rectangle
  style: {
    fill: "#4a0000"
    stroke: "#ff2020"
    stroke-width: 4
    font-color: "#ff8888"
    border-radius: 8
  }
  label: |'md
**ILLEGAL USE**
Second hash starts from
first hash's H[0..7] output state
Silent wrong digest —
no error, no crash
*Root cause of production HMAC bugs*
'|
}

# ── Initial pseudo-state ───────────────────────────────────────────────────

initial: {
  shape: circle
  width: 36
  height: 36
  style: {
    fill: "#e8d5ff"
    stroke: "#9b72cf"
    stroke-width: 3
  }
  label: ""
}

# ── Final pseudo-state ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────

final_ok: {
  shape: circle
  width: 36
  height: 36
  style: {
    fill: "#c8f0db"
    stroke: "#4caf7d"
    stroke-width: 3
    double-border: true
  }
  label: ""
}

# ── Transitions ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

initial -> UNINITIALIZED: "" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#9b72cf"
    stroke-width: 2
  }
}

UNINITIALIZED -> INITIALIZED: "sha256_init(ctx)\n[always valid]" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#4caf7d"
    stroke-width: 2
    font-color: "#4caf7d"
    bold: true
  }
}

INITIALIZED -> INITIALIZED: "sha256_update(ctx, data, 0)\n[len=0: no-op, stays INITIALIZED]" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#4a90d9"
    stroke-width: 2
    font-color: "#88bbee"
  }
}

INITIALIZED -> ACCUMULATING: "sha256_update(ctx, data, len)\n[1 ≤ len ≤ 63: fits in buf]\nbuf_len = len\ntotal_bits += len×8" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#4a90d9"
    stroke-width: 2
    font-color: "#4a90d9"
    bold: true
  }
}

INITIALIZED -> INITIALIZED: "sha256_update(ctx, data, len)\n[len = 64k exactly]\nPhase 2: k blocks compressed\nbuf_len stays 0" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#4a90d9"
    stroke-width: 2
    stroke-dash: 4
    font-color: "#88bbee"
  }
}

ACCUMULATING -> ACCUMULATING: "sha256_update(ctx, data, len)\n[bytes fit without filling buf]\nbuf_len ∈ [1,63] → buf_len' ∈ [1,63]" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#4a90d9"
    stroke-width: 2
    font-color: "#4a90d9"
  }
}

ACCUMULATING -> BLOCK_BOUNDARY: "sha256_update detects buf_len reaches 64\n[Phase 1: partial buf completes]\nTrigger: sha256_compress(H, buf)" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#e6a020"
    stroke-width: 2
    font-color: "#e6a020"
    bold: true
  }
}

BLOCK_BOUNDARY -> INITIALIZED: "[no remaining bytes after flush]\nbuf_len = 0" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#e6a020"
    stroke-width: 2
    stroke-dash: 3
    font-color: "#e6a020"
  }
}

BLOCK_BOUNDARY -> ACCUMULATING: "[remaining bytes > 0 after flush]\nbuf_len = remaining ∈ [1,63]" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#e6a020"
    stroke-width: 2
    stroke-dash: 3
    font-color: "#e6a020"
  }
}

INITIALIZED -> FINALIZED: "sha256_finalize(ctx, digest)\n[buf_len=0 → append 0x80 at buf[0]]\nused=1 ≤ 56 → single block\ncompress(H, buf)\nserialize H[0..7] → digest[0..31]" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#e05050"
    stroke-width: 2
    font-color: "#e05050"
    bold: true
  }
}

ACCUMULATING -> FINALIZED: "sha256_finalize(ctx, digest)\n[buf_len ∈ 1..55 → single block path]\n[buf_len ∈ 56..63 → two-block path]\nPad + compress + serialize" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#e05050"
    stroke-width: 2
    font-color: "#e05050"
    bold: true
  }
}

FINALIZED -> INITIALIZED: "sha256_init(ctx)\n[MANDATORY reset before reuse]\nH reset to SHA256_INITIAL_HASH\nbuf_len = 0, total_bits = 0" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#4caf7d"
    stroke-width: 3
    font-color: "#4caf7d"
    bold: true
  }
}

FINALIZED -> final_ok: "digest consumed\nby caller" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#e05050"
    stroke-width: 2
    font-color: "#cc8888"
  }
}

# ── ILLEGAL transition ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────

FINALIZED -> ILLEGAL_USE: "sha256_update(ctx, ...)\nwithout sha256_init()\n\n⚠ ILLEGAL — no crash, no error\nSecond hash inherits H from first\nSilently wrong digest" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#ff2020"
    stroke-width: 4
    stroke-dash: 5
    font-color: "#ff4040"
    bold: true
  }
  target-arrowhead: {
    shape: arrow
    style.filled: true
  }
}

# ── Annotation panels ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────

guard_note: |'md
**buf_len boundary cases in finalize()**
| `buf_len` on entry | `used` after 0x80 | Path |
|---|---|---|
| 0 | 1 | single block |
| 55 | 56 | single block (56 ≤ 56) |
| 56 | 57 | **two blocks** (57 > 56) ← trap |
| 63 | 64 | two blocks |

`total_bits` = Σ(len×8) — not `buf_len×8`
'| {
  near: bottom-left
  style: {
    fill: "#1a1a2e"
    stroke: "#4a90d9"
    stroke-width: 1
    font-color: "#c8e0ff"
    border-radius: 6
  }
}

reuse_note: |'md
**Context reuse pattern (correct)**
c
sha256_init(&ctx);          // reset H, buf_len, total_bits
sha256_update(&ctx, ...);
sha256_finalize(&ctx, digest1);

sha256_init(&ctx);          // MUST re-init
sha256_update(&ctx, ...);
sha256_finalize(&ctx, digest2);

Omitting second `sha256_init()` → ILLEGAL path
'| {
  near: bottom-right
  style: {
    fill: "#1a1a2e"
    stroke: "#4caf7d"
    stroke-width: 1
    font-color: "#c8f0db"
    border-radius: 6
  }
}